# Dev Branch Workflow

- Default to working on `dev` unless the user explicitly asks to use a different branch.
- Before starting implementation, check the current branch and switch to `dev` if needed.
- Keep changes in small, traceable commits during substantial work so history is easy to backtrack.
- Prefer multiple focused commits over one large commit when the work naturally breaks into reviewable steps.
- Use `main` for release integration only after `dev` work is ready.
